        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "$curr = new Zend_Currency('pl_PL');\r\necho $curr->toCurrency('1234567.6789', array('display' => Zend_Currency::USE_SYMBOL)); \/\/ you get: \"1 234 567,68 z\u0142\"\r\necho $curr->toCurrency('1234567.6789', array('display' => Zend_Currency::NO_SYMBOL)); \/\/ you get: \"1234567,68\", should be \"1 234 567,68\"\r\n\r\nUsing Zend_Currency::NO_SYMBOL the formatting ignores grouping. The output should be: \"1 234 567,68\". I suppose it is dependent on Zend_Locale, but don't know on which part exactly. The above works fine for example for locale \"de_AT\"."
        },
